(1) Where the Director reasonably suspects that harm has been or is likely to be caused to the environment by any person’s activity, he may serve on that person an environmental restoration notice requiring that person to take action within 21 days of the service of the notice, to remedy or prevent the harm to the environment as may be specified in the notice.
* An environmental restoration notice shall specify clearly and in a manner that may be precisely understood -
<\li1>
